============================================================
PHASE 15 OBJECTIVE
============================================================

Build the final production GA and commercial launch layer for zDash.

Main goals:

1. Expand marketplace into a certified AI Agent / Plugin marketplace
2. Add partner submission and certification workflow
3. Add marketplace revenue-share ledger shell
4. Add plugin/agent SBOM and package scanning shell
5. Add agent quality score and trust badge system
6. Add public marketplace storefront
7. Add partner portal and certification dashboard
8. Add public cloud GA launch gates
9. Add final production readiness score
10. Add reliability validation suite
11. Add load-test and chaos-test dry-run framework
12. Add API versioning and deprecation policy system
13. Add customer lifecycle analytics
14. Add conversion funnel and onboarding analytics
15. Add enterprise procurement pack generator
16. Add commercial docs and customer-facing legal document templates
17. Add GA release train and staged rollout manager
18. Add data residency / region policy shell
19. Add final safety validation gates
20. Add final Phase 15 tests, docs, runbooks, and acceptance checklist

IMPORTANT SAFETY RULES:
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass content approval checks.
- Do not bypass tenant isolation.
- Do not bypass billing entitlements.
- Do not bypass governance policies.
- Do not bypass plugin security review.
- Do not publish marketplace packages without certification.
- Do not expose secrets in marketplace metadata, logs, reports, telemetry, legal docs, GA packs, exports, or storefront pages.
- Marketplace submissions must be sandboxed and review-gated.
- Load testing and chaos testing must be dry-run/safe by default.
- GA launch must be blocked if safety gates fail.
- Revenue-share system must be ledger-only/mock by default; no real payout movement.
- Legal/commercial templates are operational placeholders, not legal advice.

