============================================================
IMPORTANT IMPLEMENTATION RULES
============================================================

- Do not use pseudocode.
- Do not skip files.
- Do not remove Phase 1–14 behavior.
- Keep all existing backend tests passing.
- Keep all existing frontend tests passing.
- Keep mobile tests passing.
- Keep desktop tests passing.
- Keep SDK tests passing.
- Use typed Python where reasonable.
- Use TypeScript types.
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.x style.
- Never hardcode secrets.
- Never expose secrets in frontend, mobile, desktop, SDKs, marketplace, telemetry, analytics, reports, commercial docs, or logs.
- Never collect raw API keys, raw prompts, raw secrets, raw trading credentials, raw broker credentials, or private keys in analytics.
- Never enable live trading by default.
- Never enable real social posting by default.
- Never enable real IoT power actions by default.
- Never bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Never bypass content approval checks.
- Never bypass tenant isolation.
- Never bypass billing entitlements.
- Never bypass governance policies.
- Never publish uncertified marketplace listings.
- Never run destructive chaos tests by default.
- Keep revenue-share ledger dry-run/accounting-only.
- Keep legal/commercial documents template-only.
- Keep public GA blocked until final safety gate passes.
- Keep code modular, production-ready, and ready for zDash v2.0 GA release.

Now generate the complete Phase 15 implementation.
